@startuml

title Ideal Email Reminder Sequence Diagram

actor User

participant "Frontend (Website)" as FE
participant "Apache\n(HTTP Server)" as Apache

box "Laravel Application" #LightGreen
  participant "Middleware" as MW
  participant "Controller" as C
  participant "Inventory Service" as Service
  participant "Messaging Service" as MessageService
  participant "Eloquent ORM" as ORM
end box

participant "Email Service SMTP" as Email
participant "Gmail" as Gmail
database "MariaDB Database" as DB

note right of User
IMPORTANT: This sequence assumes normal system operation. If a failure
occurs at any layer, the system returns an error message
and prompts the user to retry. It is also assumed the user is
authenticated/authorized.
end note


== Inventory Request Response ==
User -> FE: Submit inventory request
activate User
activate FE

FE -> Apache: POST /borrowRequest
activate Apache
Apache -> MW: Forward request
deactivate Apache

activate MW
MW -> C: Pass validated request
deactivate MW

activate C
C -> Service: createBorrowRequest()
activate Service

Service -> ORM: Check item availability
activate ORM
ORM -> DB: Query item status
activate DB
DB --> ORM: Availability result
deactivate DB
ORM --> Service: Available?
deactivate ORM

alt Item available
    Service -> ORM: Save borrow request
    activate ORM
    ORM -> DB: Insert borrow request
    activate DB
    DB --> ORM: Request saved
    deactivate DB
    ORM --> Service: Request persisted
    deactivate ORM

    Service --> C: Request approved
     activate Email
    C -> Email: Send approval email
    activate Gmail
    Email -> Gmail: Send through Gmail
    Gmail -> Email: Email sent through
    deactivate Gmail
    Email --> C: Email sent confirmation
    deactivate Email

else Item unavailable
    Service --> C: Request rejected
    activate Email
    C -> Email: Send rejection email
     activate Gmail
    Email -> Gmail: Send through Gmail
    Gmail -> Email: Email sent through
    deactivate Gmail
    
    Email --> C: Email sent confirmation
    deactivate Email
end

deactivate Service
C --> FE: Response
deactivate C

FE --> User: Display confirmation
deactivate FE
deactivate User


== Message Reminder Email ==
note over MessageService,Email: Triggered if user doesn't respond in 15 minutes

User -> FE: Open messages / check request status
activate User
activate FE

FE -> Apache: GET /messages
activate Apache
Apache -> MW: Forward request
deactivate Apache

activate MW
MW -> C: Pass validated request
deactivate MW

activate C
C -> MessageService: checkMessageTimeout()
activate MessageService

MessageService -> ORM: Check last message timestamp
activate ORM
ORM -> DB: Query latest message time
activate DB
DB --> ORM: Last message time
deactivate DB
ORM --> MessageService: Timestamp result
deactivate ORM

alt No response in 15 minutes
    MessageService -> Email: Send reminder email
    activate Email
     activate Gmail
    Email -> Gmail: Send through Gmail
    Gmail -> Email: Email sent through
    deactivate Gmail
    Email --> MessageService: Reminder sent
    deactivate Email
else User already responded
    note right of MessageService: No email sent
end

deactivate MessageService
C --> FE: Response
deactivate C

FE --> User: Display message status
deactivate FE
deactivate User


== User Ban Notification Email ==

note over C,Email: Triggered immediately when a user account is banned

User -> FE: Attempt login or access system
activate User
activate FE

FE -> Apache: POST /login
activate Apache
Apache -> MW: Forward request
deactivate Apache

activate MW
MW -> C: Pass validated request
deactivate MW

activate C
C -> ORM: Check user status
activate ORM
ORM -> DB: Query user record
activate DB
DB --> ORM: User status = banned
deactivate DB
ORM --> C: Status returned
deactivate ORM

C -> Email: Send ban notification email
activate Email
 activate Gmail
    Email -> Gmail: Send through Gmail
    Gmail -> Email: Email sent through
    deactivate Gmail
Email --> C: Ban email sent
deactivate Email

C --> FE: Access denied (user banned)
deactivate C

FE --> User: Display ban message
deactivate FE
deactivate User

@enduml